The partisanship and orientation is greater today than it was in the mid-1990s, and it turns out that there's a bigger ideological divide between Obama and the congressional Republicans than there was between the Republicans and Bill Clinton.
At the same time, activists on both sides see 2010 as a prelude to a more important election in 2012.
