Red Bull has set up a high-tech plant about 30 miles outside London to design and manufacture its racing cars.
These are two buildings that are off limits to visitors, especially journalists.
Everything that happens here is considered a "great secret".
The project has 580 participants, including two pilots - champion Vettel and Mark Webber.
The hero of Red Bull is undoubtedly the new Formula One champion Sebastian Vettel.
