Zapatero and the red German lines
Berlin has decided to keep the euro, but it has set conditions for the whole Union.
The market tensions have provoked a two-pronged government response.
On the one hand, José Luis Zapatero proposed new adaptation measures, from tax cuts for SMEs, to the regulation of private intermediation agencies, to the abolition of the €426 for unemployed without benefits, to the privatisation of 49% of AENA (Spanish Airports and Air Traffic Management), the managers of Barajas and El Prat airports and 30% of the State Lottery.
