The Republican leader will allow the party to vote secretly on its continuance.
Huguet proposes a more plural executive and an end to the meeting system.
Joan Puigcercós seems to have found a recipe for fighting the several internal revolts within the ERC (Catalan Left Republican Party) that have failed to produce results due to the loss of 11 MPs and half the vote.
The party chairman is aware that his gesture of resignation seems insufficient to the supporters of former leader José Luis Caroda-Rovira, and he also knows that the influence of this sector is now as weakened as his leader himself, and that he absolutely cannot make him worry as he did about other extinct currents.
That's why the leader of the Left will try to win new criticism by winking his eye to help him turn to the general election.
