with elements of magical realism, it tells the story of a famous witch who played clouds, brought back people who had gone far, or restored the integrity lost by a virgin, a tale that then turned to speak America, a great novel that from the beginning was not without its own chroniclers who told it, and here is a quote from Bernal Díaz del Castillo, who criticizes the exaggeration of the stories of the conquering captains.
